{
  "stem": "20142.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And of course, the Germans were saying to us, take a look what a big army we-- we are fighting.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "No wonder we got it so quickly.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Of course, all this, we knew that it was a great propaganda for the Germans to-- to exploit the people and make them believe that a new regime, a new era is coming for them to experience.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] one day we were already in camp, and we realized that something must have been happening because they needed the workforce.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they start taking from the camps people for work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And this started, actually, in August of 1943.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I beg--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the material for the dirt field ran out, then they sent us to the munition factory in Lublin.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the supervisors in this munition factory and in-- and in the aircraft factory were Polish people from the city of Lublin.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from them, we got the news that-- what's going on on the frontiers, and so on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some of the Germans were, some are killing us by saying, well, I wonder how well you gonna take care of us when we're gonna lose the war.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were surprised to hear, because never ever before, even from the elder Germans, we could hear words like this.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when I was in munition factory, somebody contact me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the only way, I mentioned once before, that I had responded to the word [NON-ENGLISH] when somebody [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] mentioned to me the word [NON-ENGLISH], I looked and I didn't pay attention.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then a Polish man came over to me and said, do you know what [NON-ENGLISH] is?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I still looked at him, I didn't answer him, I kept going, doing my work.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
